### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

When returning multiple values from the request function, the request property received in the loader function contains the undefined type.

```ts
request: () => {
      const id = this.id(), otherValue = 'example';
      return id != null ? {id, otherValue} : undefined;
    },
    loader: ({request, abortSignal}) =>
```
request() return type: `{ id: number; otherValue: string; } | undefined`

In loader function params, i expect request to have type: `{ id: number; otherValue: string; }` but it includes undefined : `NoInfer<{id: number; otherValue: string; } | undefined>`

This seems related to this [issue](https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/60594)
```ts
export interface ResourceLoaderParams<R> {
  request: Exclude<NoInfer<R>, undefined>;
  abortSignal: AbortSignal;
  previous: {
    status: ResourceStatus;
  };
}
```
One of the comments in that issue suggests that `NoInfer<Exclude<R, undefined>>` works


